sec.p:
Based on the information from the COMP practice, as it is reflected in the published minutes of its plenary meetings, and in the context of the provisions of the orphan framework and the relevant available guidance, there are three points that in general need to be met in order to justify the medical plausibility:
data with the specific product as applied for designation are required; the proposed product exists and a stage of development can be identified;
results from studies with the product are required in either specific models of the condition, or in patients affected by the condition as applied for designation;
the endpoints studied have to be clinically relevant and the results adequate to allow for scientific claims on improvement upon administration of the product under review.
